body:
@rringham You download the wheel and install it with `pip` like the build on the website, but you will be doing that locally. 

For instance, [select the most recent working build](http://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Nightly/job/nightly-win/) (blue) from the list on the left, choose the version you want, CPU or GPU, and download the wheel. 
On your terminal `cd` to the directory you downloaded the build on and install it with `pip install <name-of-the-wheel>`
